edu.smu.tspell.wordnet
Interface NounSynset

All Superinterfaces:
Synset
All Known Implementing Classes:
NounReferenceSynset
public interface NounSynset
extends Synset

Represents a synset that corresponds to a noun meaning.

See Also:
Five Papers on WordNet ("Nouns in WordNet: A Lexical Inheritance System")

Method Detail

getHypernyms

public NounSynset[] getHypernyms()
                          throws WordNetException
Returns the direct hypernyms (superordinate types), if any, of this type.

For example, the hypernym of "tent" is "shelter".

Returns:
The direct hypernyms of this synset.
Throws:
WordNetException - An error occurred retrieving data.

getInstanceHypernyms

public NounSynset[] getInstanceHypernyms()
                                  throws WordNetException
Returns the instance hypernyms of this synset. An instance hyponym is a specific instance of something and the instance hypernym represents the reflexive type.

For example, the instance hypernym of "Mississippi River" is "river".

Returns:
Instance hypernyms of this synset.
Throws:
WordNetException - An error occurred retrieving data.

getHyponyms

public NounSynset[] getHyponyms()
                         throws WordNetException
Returns the direct hyponyms (subordinate type), if any, of this type.

For example, a hyponym of "shelter" is "tent".

Returns:
The direct hyponyms of this synset.
Throws:
WordNetException - An error occurred retrieving data.

getInstanceHyponyms

public NounSynset[] getInstanceHyponyms()
                                 throws WordNetException
Returns the instance hyponyms of a synset, where instance hyponyms represent specific (usually real-world) instances of something.

For example, instance hyponyms of "river" included "Mississippi River", "Amazon River", etc.

Returns:
Instance hyponyms of this synset.
Throws:
WordNetException - An error occurred retrieving data.

Member holonyms of this synset.

WordNetException - An error occurred retrieving data.

getPartHolonyms

public NounSynset[] getPartHolonyms()
                             throws WordNetException
Returns the holonyms (whole that includes this part) of this type.

For example, a part holonym of "fuselage" is "airplane".

Returns:
The (possibly empty) list of holonyms for this synset.
Throws:
WordNetException - An error occurred retrieving data.

getMemberMeronyms

public NounSynset[] getMemberMeronyms()
                               throws WordNetException
Returns the member meronyms of this synset, where member meronyms are the parts that make up the whole.

For example, member meronyms of "Roman Alphabet" are "A", "B", "C", etc.

Returns:
Member parts that make up the whole represented by this synset.
Throws:
WordNetException - An error occurred retrieving data.

getPartMeronyms

public NounSynset[] getPartMeronyms()
                             throws WordNetException
Returns the meronyms (inherited parts) of this type.

For example, part meronyms for "airplane" include "wing" and "fuselage".

Returns:
The (possibly empty) list of meronyms for this synset.
Throws:
WordNetException - An error occurred retrieving data.

getSubstanceMeronyms

public NounSynset[] getSubstanceMeronyms()
                                  throws WordNetException
Returns substances that make up the thing represented by this synset.

Returns:
Substances that compose the thing represented by this synset.

WordNetException - An error occurred retrieving data.
